'''''Beyond Ynth''''' is a mobile game for [[iOS]] and [[Android (OS)|Android]] developed by German studio FDG Entertainment and released on September 10, 2010.

==Critical reception==
The game has a Metacritic score of 87% based on 7 critic reviews.<ref name="metacritic.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/ios/beyond-ynth|title=Beyond Ynth|work=Metacritic}}</ref>

AppSpy wrote "Beyond Ynth is an amazing improvement over the first in the series and while it's still a casual game at heart, the challenge is far from simple."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.appspy.com/review/4304/beyond-ynth-review|title=Beyond Ynth Review|author=Andrew Nesvadba|date=22 September 2010|work=appspy.com}}</ref> Slide To Play said "Beyond Ynth is as tough as nails due to levels crafted with high finesse. This puzzler isn't for the faint of heart."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slidetoplay.com/review/beyond-ynth-review/|title=Beyond Ynth Review|publisher=}}</ref> 148Apps wrote "One word of warning though is that the game is extremely difficult."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.148apps.com/reviews/ynth-review/|title=Beyond Ynth Review|work=148Apps}}</ref> TouchGen wrote "Beyond Ynth is a great game in the spatial puzzle genre. It can be frustrating, hard and addictive. To me this is the kind of game that is perfect for the iPhone."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.touchgen.net/beyond-ynth-review |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-10-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130930074859/http://www.touchgen.net/beyond-ynth-review |archivedate=2013-09-30 |df= }}</ref> TocuhArcade said "With 80 levels to play through plus the added replayability of obtaining gold medals for each one, Beyond Ynth will keep you busy for a long time."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://toucharcade.com/2010/09/16/beyond-ynth-review-unique-but-frustrating-puzzle-platformer/|title=Beyond Ynth Review - TouchArcade|work=TouchArcade}}</ref> GamePro said "I'd like to see new control options in an update, but otherwise this is a great platformer."<ref name="metacritic.com"/> Pocket Gamer UK wrote "A refined take on the original, Beyond Ynth brings extra knobs and bobs that take the existing formula and make it trickier, but this isn't a true step forward."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pocketgamer.co.uk/r/iPhone/Beyond+Ynth/review.asp?c=23754|title=Beyond Ynth (a.k.a. Beyond Ynth HD)|date=24 September 2010|work=Pocket Gamer}}</ref>

