[[Image:Gurglin gutz1.jpg|thumb|A Gurglin Gutz [[brain]] keychain]]
'''Gurglin Gutz''' was a toy consisting of a colorful, stylized, rubber human organ, either a [[brain]], [[heart]], [[stomach]], or [[eyeball]], immersed in a red fluid and enclosed in a thin latex ball film. The toy produced guttural gurgling and bubbling noises when squeezed, as the liquid pulsated in the rubber organ's many cavities and orifices. ''Gugling Gutz'' also came in a smaller, keychain size.

The toy was created by [[Jimmy Diresta|Jimmy DiResta]],<ref>{{cite news|last=Donovan|first=Aaron|title=NEW YORKERS & CO.; Toys and Items That Began As Found Objects|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1999/09/05/nyregion/new-yorkers-co-toys-and-items-that-began-as-found-objects.html|accessdate=21 April 2014|newspaper=The New York Times|date=September 5, 1999}}</ref> and manufactured by 4Kidz, Inc.

